I'll search for current Tokyo travel information and attractions to create a relevant itinerary.
Based on the search results, I'll create a 4-day itinerary for Tokyo starting July 4, 2025. I'll focus on combining efficient sightseeing with the best experiences the city has to offer.

Day 1 (July 4, 2025) - Arrival & Traditional Tokyo
* 8:00 AM - Arrival at 
either Haneda Airport (closest to city) or Narita International Airport

* 10:00 AM - Head to 
Asakusa, the heart of Tokyo's downtown area with ancient temples and traditional stores

* 10:30 AM - Visit Sensō-ji Temple

Opening hours: 6:30 AM - 6:00 PM (Summer timing)
Take time to explore the temple grounds and enjoy the colorful street food

* 2:00 PM - 
Visit Tokyo Imperial Palace
Note: While palace buildings are not open to public, you can explore the East Gardens
Garden hours: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM (Summer timing)

* Evening - 
Dinner at one of Tokyo's countless restaurants - the city has more Michelin-starred restaurants than any other city, plus hundreds of delicious ramen shops


Day 2 (July 5, 2025) - Modern Tokyo
* 10:00 AM - 
Explore Harajuku and Shibuya, Tokyo's trendy shopping districts

* 11:00 AM - 
Visit Takeshita Street in Harajuku
- Explore the colorful street with eccentric clothing stores
- Try local treats like crepes
- Browse anime costumes and unique fashion items

* 2:00 PM - 
Head to Shinjuku, the thriving business district with its mix of gleaming skyscrapers and atmospheric back streets with tiny bars

* Evening - 
Visit Tokyo Tower for sunset views
- The tower offers views for miles in every direction
- Located near Roppongi and Toranomon districts


Day 3 (July 6, 2025) - Shopping & Entertainment
* 10:00 AM - 
Visit Ginza
- Tokyo's most elegant and luxurious district
- Perfect for shopping and gourmet cuisine

* 2:00 PM - 
Explore Odaiba
- Features diverse attractions on reclaimed land in Tokyo Bay
- Evening highlight: bayside stroll to see the illuminated Rainbow Bridge

* Evening - 
Temple light-up viewing until 11 PM - many temple grounds remain open and are beautifully lit at night


Day 4 (July 7, 2025) - Nature & Relaxation
* 10:00 AM - 
Visit Tokyo's botanical gardens
- Enjoy seasonal colors
- Possible bird watching opportunities
- Look for species like the Kingfisher

* 2:00 PM - 
Explore Tokyo's green spaces - contrary to common perception, the city offers numerous attractive parks in the center and within short train rides

* Evening - 
Note about weather: Summer in Tokyo is hot and humid, so plan indoor activities during peak heat hours. The city can experience typhoons during this season


Transportation Tip: 
Get an IC transport

